vfs_file("WELCOME", "Welcome to ZenovOS 0.1.1.\n\nThe kernel enables paging and tracks physical memory frames. Persistent files are stored on /data using ZenovFS1.\nRun HELLO starts the ZEX1 application. Run FILEIO.ELF exercises the ELF32 loader and file syscalls.\nThe command editor accepts 511 visible or scrolled characters and retains 128 commands.\nPress F1 for the complete command reference.\n");
vfs_file("SYSTEM", "Product: ZenovOS 0.1.1\nTarget: i686-zenov-none\nBoot: legacy BIOS / FAT12\nMemory: E820 PMM + 4 KiB paging\nData: ATA PIO / ZenovFS1\nKernel: ring 0, freestanding C++17 and assembler\nApplications: ZEX1 and ELF32, ring 3, INT 0x80\nConfiguration: modular Zenov .zv includes\nConsole: VGA text mode + COM1\nCommand capacity: 511 characters\nHistory capacity: 128 commands\n");
vfs_file("STORAGE", "Persistent commands:\n  mount, df, fsck, sync, pwd, cd, ls\n  mkdir, touch, write, append\n  cat, stat, cp, mv, rm\n\nEvery file is checksummed and remains on the data image after reboot.\n");
vfs_file("APPLICATIONS", "Native ZenovOS programs can use ZEX1 or validated static ELF32.\n\nCommands:\n  apps           list installed applications\n  run HELLO      launch the ZEX1 sample\n  run FILEIO.ELF launch the ELF32 file-syscall sample\n\nWindows PE and DOS MZ .exe files are not compatible yet.\n");
vfs_file("COMMANDS", "home help info status devices disk mount df fsck sync pmm vm pwd cd ls files cat mkdir touch write append rm cp mv stat apps run cpu mem memmap uptime date time echo calc theme history bootlog limits clear reboot halt\n");
vfs_file("INSTALL", "ZenovOS 0.1.1 boots from the FAT12 system image and mounts a separate writable ATA data image. Keep both images together when using QEMU or VirtualBox. The release does not yet install itself to a physical hard disk.\n");
vfs_file("ARCHITECTURE", "The product configuration is split across kernel/config/*.zv and assembled through guarded relative include statements. Includes are recursive, cycle-checked, limited to depth 16 and forbidden from escaping the source root. The stage0 self-test compiles 200 declarations to prevent regressions to tiny source files.\n");
